<review_text>

this book provides a good overview of blacks ( slave and free ) in new york .
it 's a very good reference ( encyclopedic ) book .
my main problem with it is that leslie m. harris , the author , relies heavily ( if not entirely ) on secondary sources .
the book , then , is nothing more than a patchwork of various other more scholarly works .
hence , finding the actual primary source ( i.e .
court decision , council minutes , etc ) proves extremely difficult .
i do not recommend this book for advanced students .
