<review_text>

i was there , as were several of my fellow sitka fire department emt 's and state troopers from the sitka academy .
the 6 of us , along with two parajumpers from the canadian armed services were flown through the typhoon winds , on a helicopter , out to the williamsburgh where we spent the next 33 hours attending to the rescued passengers - literally giving them the clothes off our backs and keeping them calmed .
